      <title>Mana Regen Clickies &amp; stacking</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=235948#M235948</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;For the Devs to consider:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Mana pools keep growing. Mana regen does not. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;There are some nice mana regen clickies out there, but a rigid no stacking policy. True, there are a few that do stack, but the general rule is limited stacking.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Perhaps its time to reevaluate this? Therefor I propose: Lessen the stacking restrictions...a little. Perhaps a big mana regen item can now stack with a minor regen item. Or mana regen clickes can stack only when you're grouped, or in a raid. Or introduce a line of AA's that allow %'s of stacking mana clickes. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As a Druid, when I'm on a raid and I run out of mana, I totally useless. (please! no debate on druid abilites here!) The same applies to most casters w/o mana.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;....or a minor bump&amp;nbsp;of the&amp;nbsp;Flowing Thought cap?&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
