    <item>
      <title>Re: Mana Regen Clickies &amp; stacking</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=236898#M236898</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I respectfully disagree, and here is why:&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;1) The only players that are exceeding the FT cap of 20 (including EM5 aa's) by a significant degree are hardcore raiders.&amp;nbsp; They may have as much as FT50-FT60 in gear on, maybe even higher.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;I don't think it's much higher than that, although I could be mistaken.&amp;nbsp; Most players at L70 with decent gear will be in the FT20-FT40 range.&amp;nbsp; That increase, when compared to the mana cost of spells since Velious era as well as the manapool increase will not "break the game".&amp;nbsp; It will make regen a little faster, downtime a little shorter, but certainly won't trivialize anything.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;2) Most encounters these days are built around strategy and&amp;nbsp;class balance.&amp;nbsp; I don't believe there are many Xegony-style fights where you are required to sustain 30-40min+ of constant casting.&amp;nbsp; Therefore, the increased mana-regen will not trivialize anything.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;I would wager that most high-end content is not difficult because certain classes are running out of mana, rather it is difficult due to the demands of the encounter.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If there is a noticeable effect on the game by increasing the mana-regen to match the worn FT total, certainly some kind of scale of diminishing returns could be put in place to increase regen but respect the integrity of most encounters.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
