      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
markopaw wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I respectfully disagree, and here is why:&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;1) The only players that are exceeding the FT cap of 20 (including EM5 aa's) by a significant degree are hardcore raiders.&amp;nbsp; They may have as much as FT50-FT60 in gear on, maybe even higher.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;I don't think it's much higher than that, although I could be mistaken.&amp;nbsp; Most players at L70 with decent gear will be in the FT20-FT40 range.&amp;nbsp; That increase, when compared to the mana cost of spells since Velious era as well as the manapool increase will not "break the game".&amp;nbsp; It will make regen a little faster, downtime a little shorter, but certainly won't trivialize anything.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;2) Most encounters these days are built around strategy and&amp;nbsp;class balance.&amp;nbsp; I don't believe there are many Xegony-style fights where you are required to sustain 30-40min+ of constant casting.&amp;nbsp; Therefore, the increased mana-regen will not trivialize anything.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;I would wager that most high-end content is not difficult because certain classes are running out of mana, rather it is difficult due to the demands of the encounter.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If there is a noticeable effect on the game by increasing the mana-regen to match the worn FT total, certainly some kind of scale of diminishing returns could be put in place to increase regen but respect the integrity of most encounters.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Here's the thing though..a lot of those "strategic encounters" where people would have ft 50-80 also have times where there's an extended full burn (or 15).&amp;nbsp; What would 200 to 550 more mana regen per min due to the encounters in DoB tier 2 (besides gimp them into oblivion)?&amp;nbsp; Razorthorne with nobody running OOM or even close?&amp;nbsp; The way encounters are set up, they're balanced (or seem to be) around an appropriate gearing level and expected mana regen/dps potentials raid wide..when one of those facets of an encounter greatly exceeds what it was designed around, the challenge of that encounter goes away.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I can see 5 more FT/mana regen, possibly 10..if new content later this year(?) is really difficult, but beyond that I think it's overkill and would trivial the existing content.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The difficulty in acquiring ft is very low.&amp;nbsp; The one-time reward augs(most of them) from DODH found there way onto backpack items the day they showed up on my cursor.&amp;nbsp; It's almost trivial, if you go through DoN, LDoN etc to get 25-45ft.&amp;nbsp; I have around 45 worn atm..and I haven't worked at it since PoP.&amp;nbsp; Some people might lose some hps/mana if they converted a lot of augs to ft(if the cap were removed) but that'd be their choice.&amp;nbsp; I think a wizard would be better off with an additional ft30 instead of 500 mana..&lt;/P&gt;</description>
