      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;This is not about which class can regen mana faster, or why they should, or how they do it....this is about a long neglected aspect of the game.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Remember, mana pools are increasing.....mana regen is not.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;We can try some innovative ideas on mana savings...raising specization skills, adjusting the bottom range of conservation items. We can think about raising FT caps and stacking mana item clickies. We can consider lowering mana costs. We can raise the issue of AE's overwriting our mana regen buffs...&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;...but another useless rant about who's class is best is not going to be productive in ANY WAY! If you feel the urge to 'add' a CLASS statement here you are torpedoing this thread. STOP IT!&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;My orginal post was about stacking mana regen clickies. I have added some other ideas. Ideas that wil effect the entire game, not just one class over another. Becasue fo this we need to proced VERY carefully. This is a major apple cart, we don't want to upset it.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;IF a mob is supposed to attack our mana regen, then we have to trust the SoE will balance the fight around this fact. But are trash mobs supposed to do this as well? (sorry, don't have any flashy examples right off the top of my head) IF a boss mob is supposed to attack our mana regen, where is our chance to defend? Where is the player SKILL involved? Or do I just sit there and take it....&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Many threads have been posted about mana regen abilites being overwritten by AE's, so far I've not seen anything about repairing this. Is it a bug? A glitch? Is it working as intended? Are we casters supposed to go OOM during a battle and sit there completely useless? (a burden on the rest of the guild?) That's not game balance, that's mean spirited. Total lack of SoE communication about this is frustrating. Lets get the official word, please.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I also play a ranger. Freshly rez I can stand up and start contributing to a fight without a sinlge buff and zero mana/end. Granted, not much....but still some. AS a caster freshly rezed I can do....nothing. But med. Or get a mana dump from a necro. (do necros like that? I think not.) I can click a mod rod, but I had to pester a Mage for that. I can't cast my own mana regen buffs....but I CAN CLICK MY MANA REGEN CLICKES! &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;...Which brings us full circle....how about loosening the restriction on stacking mana regen clickes? Hmmmmmm? All I want to do is contribute to my guild and get back into the fight. In short...I want to PLAY, not sit around and watch helplessly as my team continues on. Is THAT too much to ask?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</description>
