&lt;P&gt;I just had another thought about stacking mana regen clickies.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;EG: Dead, freshly rezed, zero mana, zero class-specific-mana-regen-buffs.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Goal: To get back into the game asap.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Since I have no mana and no player cast mana regen buffs (C6, SA,etc) how about allowing ALL mana regen clickes to stack with full benefits UNTIL A PLAYER CASTS ONE ON ME. Or I cast one myself?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I loot my corpse, open my bag of clickes and cast what I have and they stack....but when I get any player buffs(including self buffs) ALL the clickes go poof! This would be something only usefull under certain conditions and wouldn't overpower the casters under normal conditions.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Or....perhaps it's time to investigate being rezed with a minimum amount of mana....not the 50% that you get in MM's...say 10% or so. Just enough to be able to contribute to the fight in a small way, or be able to rebuff myself and get back into my 'normal' mana regen abilities.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Or... perhaps 'rez effects' allow us to cast class specific mana regen buffs for no cost? No other type of spell, just Mask, Oak, C6, Lich, whatever?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;There are solutions out there, we just have to open our minds and accept that we're not going to get outragious mana regen capablites.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
